                      <span>1</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2004-01-07</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>This is a nice book that I have read from time to time. It is a somewhat academic guide to the handling or the managing the problems of a company or organization during times of stress. It is not a "Dummies Guide to ...", but it is more philosphical with broader guidelines. I like his one point about keeping three months of cash available or liquid assets to maintain liquidity during the crisis. When I was a student in Boston I had a famous economics Professor and he kept repeating "add 10% for uncertainty" - the three months is something that sticks in one's mind years later and is always a good guide.<P>Good book in the Drucker style, and one of his shorter books.<P>Jack in Toronto.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Still the best</div>
